      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def run_protocol(a=1.2, b=1.0, T=1.0, dt=1e-3, x0=1.0, protocol=\"AB\"):\n",
        "    x = x0\n",
        "    steps = int(T / dt)\n",
        "    half = steps // 2\n",
        "    history = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(steps):\n",
        "        gate = protocol[0] if i < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "            x += (a * x) * dt\n",
        "        else:  # gate == \"B\"\n",
        "            x -= (b * x) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "        x = max(0.0, x)  # irreversibility / depletion floor\n",
        "        history.append(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return np.array(history)\n",
        "\n",
        "x_ab = run_protocol(protocol=\"AB\")\n",
        "x_ba = run_protocol(protocol=\"BA\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final x (AB):\", x_ab[-1])\n",
        "print(\"Final x (BA):\", x_ba[-1])\n",
        "print(\"Δx:\", x_ab[-1] - x_ba[-1])"
      ]
    },

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def run_protocol(a=1.2, b=6.0, T=1.0, dt=1e-4, x0=0.05, protocol=\"AB\"):\n",
        "    x = x0\n",
        "    steps = int(T / dt)\n",
        "    half = steps // 2\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(steps):\n",
        "        gate = protocol[0] if i < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "        if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "            x += (a * x) * dt\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            x -= (b * x) * dt\n",
        "        x = max(0.0, x)  # floor bites when damage is strong enough\n",
        "    return x\n",
        "\n",
        "x_ab = run_protocol(protocol=\"AB\")\n",
        "x_ba = run_protocol(protocol=\"BA\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final x (AB):\", x_ab)\n",
        "print(\"Final x (BA):\", x_ba)\n",
        "print(\"Δx:\", x_ab - x_ba)"

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def run_protocol(a=1.2, b=1.0, T=1.0, dt=1e-3, x0=0.2, xmin=0.15, protocol=\"AB\"):\n",
        "    x = x0\n",
        "    steps = int(T / dt)\n",
        "    half = steps // 2\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(steps):\n",
        "        gate = protocol[0] if i < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "            # Build only works if x is above a minimal viability/connectivity threshold\n",
        "            if x >= xmin:\n",
        "                x += (a * x) * dt\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            x -= (b * x) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "        x = max(0.0, x)\n",
        "    return x\n",
        "\n",
        "x_ab = run_protocol(protocol=\"AB\")\n",
        "x_ba = run_protocol(protocol=\"BA\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final x (AB):\", x_ab)\n",
        "print(\"Final x (BA):\", x_ba)\n",
        "print(\"Δx:\", x_ab - x_ba)"
      ],

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def run(protocol=\"BA\", steps=2000, x0=0.20, xmin=0.15,\n",
        "        a=3.0, b=2.0, chiral_bias=0.0):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Two enantiomer lineages: L and R.\n",
        "    A-gate: growth only if x >= xmin (admissibility threshold).\n",
        "    B-gate: damage always acts.\n",
        "    chirality: small bias in growth rate (L gets +bias, R gets -bias).\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    xL = x0\n",
        "    xR = x0\n",
        "    half = steps // 2\n",
        "    dt = 1.0 / steps\n",
        "\n",
        "    aL = a * (1.0 + chiral_bias)\n",
        "    aR = a * (1.0 - chiral_bias)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(steps):\n",
        "        gate = protocol[0] if i < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "            if xL >= xmin:\n",
        "                xL += (aL * xL) * dt\n",
        "            if xR >= xmin:\n",
        "                xR += (aR * xR) * dt\n",
        "        else:  # gate == \"B\"\n",
        "            xL -= (b * xL) * dt\n",
        "            xR -= (b * xR) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "        xL = max(0.0, xL)\n",
        "        xR = max(0.0, xR)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return xL, xR, (xL - xR)\n",
        "\n",
        "def demo():\n",
        "    for protocol in [\"AB\", \"BA\"]:\n",
        "        # Non-chiral: L and R identical\n",
        "        xL, xR, dx = run(protocol=protocol, chiral_bias=0.0)\n",
        "        print(f\"{protocol} non-chiral  -> xL={xL:.6f}, xR={xR:.6f}, Δ={dx:.3e}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Chiral: tiny bias (e.g. 1%)\n",
        "        xL, xR, dx = run(protocol=protocol, chiral_bias=0.01)\n",
        "        print(f\"{protocol} chiral(1%)  -> xL={xL:.6f}, xR={xR:.6f}, Δ={dx:.6f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "demo()"
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def simulate_chiral_toy(\n",
        "    steps=4000,\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,\n",
        "    b=2.0,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.0,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"growth\",   # \"growth\", \"damage\", or \"both\"\n",
        "    dt=None,\n",
        "):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Two lineages: L and R. Two gates: A and B.\n",
        "      - Gate A: multiplicative growth if x >= xmin (admissibility threshold).\n",
        "      - Gate B: multiplicative damage (erosion).\n",
        "    Chirality can bias growth, damage, or both.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns:\n",
        "      t, xL, xR, adv, aoi_like\n",
        "        adv[t] = xL[t] - xR[t]\n",
        "        aoi_like = ∫ [adv(t)]_+ dt (discrete sum)\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    if dt is None:\n",
        "        dt = 1.0 / steps\n",
        "\n",
        "    half = steps // 2\n",
        "    xL = float(x0)\n",
        "    xR = float(x0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Build chiral modifiers\n",
        "    aL = a * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    aR = a * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    bL = b * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "    bR = b * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "\n",
        "    t = np.arange(steps) * dt\n",
        "    xLs = np.zeros(steps, dtype=float)\n",
        "    xRs = np.zeros(steps, dtype=float)\n",
        "    adv = np.zeros(steps, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(steps):\n",
        "        gate = protocol[0] if i < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "            if xL >= xmin:\n",
        "                xL += (aL * xL) * dt\n",
        "            if xR >= xmin:\n",
        "                xR += (aR * xR) * dt\n",
        "        else:  # gate == \"B\"\n",
        "            xL -= (bL * xL) * dt\n",
        "            xR -= (bR * xR) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Physical floors\n",
        "        if xL < 0.0:\n",
        "            xL = 0.0\n",
        "        if xR < 0.0:\n",
        "            xR = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        xLs[i] = xL\n",
        "        xRs[i] = xR\n",
        "        adv[i] = xL - xR\n",
        "\n",
        "    aoi_like = float(np.sum(np.maximum(adv, 0.0)) * dt)\n",
        "    return t, xLs, xRs, adv, aoi_like\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def run_sweep(grid, steps=4000):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    grid: list of dicts. Each dict contains parameters for simulate_chiral_toy.\n",
        "    Returns a DataFrame with summary metrics + stores timeseries in a dict.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    rows = []\n",
        "    series = {}\n",
        "    for idx, params in enumerate(grid):\n",
        "        t, xL, xR, adv, aoi_like = simulate_chiral_toy(steps=steps, **params)\n",
        "        key = f\"case_{idx:04d}\"\n",
        "        series[key] = {\"t\": t, \"xL\": xL, \"xR\": xR, \"adv\": adv, \"params\": params}\n",
        "\n",
        "        rows.append({\n",
        "            \"case\": key,\n",
        "            \"protocol\": params.get(\"protocol\", \"AB\"),\n",
        "            \"chirality_in\": params.get(\"chirality_in\", \"growth\"),\n",
        "            \"chiral_bias\": params.get(\"chiral_bias\", 0.0),\n",
        "            \"xmin\": params.get(\"xmin\", 0.0),\n",
        "            \"a\": params.get(\"a\", 0.0),\n",
        "            \"b\": params.get(\"b\", 0.0),\n",
        "            \"x0\": params.get(\"x0\", 0.0),\n",
        "            \"final_xL\": xL[-1],\n",
        "            \"final_xR\": xR[-1],\n",
        "            \"final_adv\": adv[-1],\n",
        "            \"peak_adv\": float(np.max(adv)),\n",
        "            \"aoi_like\": aoi_like,\n",
        "        })\n",
        "    return pd.DataFrame(rows), series\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_growth_curves(series, cases=None, show_adv=False, title=\"AOI chirality toy sweep\"):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Plots xL and xR vs time for selected cases.\n",
        "    If show_adv=True, also plots advantage xL-xR.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    if cases is None:\n",
        "        cases = list(series.keys())\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"time\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x(t)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    for key in cases:\n",
        "        s = series[key]\n",
        "        t = s[\"t\"]\n",
        "        plt.plot(t, s[\"xL\"], label=f\"{key}  L  {s['params']}\")\n",
        "        plt.plot(t, s[\"xR\"], linestyle=\"--\", label=f\"{key}  R\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend(fontsize=7)\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    if show_adv:\n",
        "        plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "        plt.title(title + \"  (advantage: L-R)\")\n",
        "        plt.xlabel(\"time\")\n",
        "        plt.ylabel(\"adv(t)\")\n",
        "        for key in cases:\n",
        "            s = series[key]\n",
        "            plt.plot(s[\"t\"], s[\"adv\"], label=f\"{key}  adv\")\n",
        "        plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "        plt.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
        "        plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "        plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def make_grid():\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Example sweep grid. Tweak as you like.\n",
        "    Sweeps:\n",
        "      - protocol: AB vs BA\n",
        "      - chirality_in: growth vs damage vs both\n",
        "      - chiral_bias: 0, 0.01, 0.03\n",
        "      - xmin: 0.10, 0.15\n",
        "      - b: 1.5, 2.0, 2.5\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    protocols = [\"AB\", \"BA\"]\n",
        "    chirality_modes = [\"growth\", \"damage\", \"both\"]\n",
        "    biases = [0.0, 0.01, 0.03]\n",
        "    xmins = [0.10, 0.15]\n",
        "    bs = [1.5, 2.0, 2.5]\n",
        "\n",
        "    base = {\"x0\": 0.20, \"a\": 3.0, \"b\": 2.0, \"xmin\": 0.15}\n",
        "    grid = []\n",
        "    for protocol in protocols:\n",
        "        for chirality_in in chirality_modes:\n",
        "            for chiral_bias in biases:\n",
        "                for xmin in xmins:\n",
        "                    for b in bs:\n",
        "                        params = dict(base)\n",
        "                        params[\"protocol\"] = protocol\n",
        "                        params[\"chirality_in\"] = chirality_in\n",
        "                        params[\"chiral_bias\"] = chiral_bias\n",
        "                        params[\"xmin\"] = xmin\n",
        "                        params[\"b\"] = b\n",
        "                        grid.append(params)\n",
        "    return grid\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    grid = make_grid()\n",
        "    summary_df, series = run_sweep(grid, steps=4000)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Show top “wins” by AOI-like accumulation (larger = stronger cumulative chiral advantage)\n",
        "    print(summary_df.sort_values(\"aoi_like\", ascending=False).head(20).to_string(index=False))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Plot a few illustrative cases (edit selection however you like)\n",
        "    top_cases = summary_df.sort_values(\"aoi_like\", ascending=False)[\"case\"].head(3).tolist()\n",
        "    plot_growth_curves(series, cases=top_cases, show_adv=True, title=\"Top 3 by AOI-like advantage\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Also compare AB vs BA at a fixed parameter choice\n",
        "    fixed = {\"x0\": 0.20, \"a\": 3.0, \"b\": 2.0, \"xmin\": 0.15, \"chiral_bias\": 0.01, \"chirality_in\": \"both\"}\n",
        "    grid2 = [\n",
        "        dict(fixed, protocol=\"AB\"),\n",
        "        dict(fixed, protocol=\"BA\"),\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "    summary2, series2 = run_sweep(grid2, steps=4000)\n",
        "    print(\"\\nAB vs BA fixed-case summary:\\n\", summary2.to_string(index=False))\n",
        "    plot_growth_curves(series2, cases=summary2[\"case\"].tolist(), show_adv=True, title=\"AB vs BA (fixed)\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {

            "      case protocol chirality_in  chiral_bias  xmin   a   b  x0  final_xL  final_xR  final_adv  peak_adv  aoi_like\n",

            "case_0001       BA         both         0.01  0.15 3.0 2.0 0.2  0.074297  0.072825   0.001472  0.001472  0.001265\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x400 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "def seasonal_factor(day, period_days=365, amp=0.6, phase=0.0):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Returns a multiplier in [1-amp, 1+amp] following a sinusoid over the year.\n",
        "    amp=0 -> no seasonality.\n",
        "    phase shifts the season (0 means peak at day ~period/4).\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    return 1.0 + amp * np.sin(2.0 * np.pi * (day / period_days) + phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "def simulate_year(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",          # \"AB\" means A then B each day; \"BA\" means B then A\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,                  # base growth rate in A window\n",
        "    b=2.0,                  # base damage rate in B window (UV analogue)\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",    # \"growth\", \"damage\", or \"both\"\n",
        "    seasonal_uv_amp=0.6,    # seasonality strength for UV/damage (0 -> none)\n",
        "    seasonal_a_amp=0.0,     # optional seasonality for growth/resources\n",
        "    uv_phase=0.0,\n",
        "    a_phase=0.0,\n",
        "):\n",
        "    dt = 1.0 / steps_per_day\n",
        "    half = steps_per_day // 2\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Chiral modifiers\n",
        "    aL0 = a * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    aR0 = a * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    bL0 = b * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "    bR0 = b * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "\n",
        "    xL = float(x0)\n",
        "    xR = float(x0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Store daily outputs (end-of-day)\n",
        "    xL_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    xR_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    adv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    uv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    a_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for day in range(days):\n",
        "        uv_mult = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_uv_amp, phase=uv_phase)\n",
        "        a_mult  = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_a_amp,  phase=a_phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Daily effective rates\n",
        "        aL = aL0 * a_mult\n",
        "        aR = aR0 * a_mult\n",
        "        bL = bL0 * uv_mult\n",
        "        bR = bR0 * uv_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Run one day with two windows (A and B) in the specified order\n",
        "        for step in range(steps_per_day):\n",
        "            gate = protocol[0] if step < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "            if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "                if xL >= xmin:\n",
        "                    xL += (aL * xL) * dt\n",
        "                if xR >= xmin:\n",
        "                    xR += (aR * xR) * dt\n",
        "            else:  # gate == \"B\" (UV/damage window)\n",
        "                xL -= (bL * xL) * dt\n",
        "                xR -= (bR * xR) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Floors\n",
        "            if xL < 0.0: xL = 0.0\n",
        "            if xR < 0.0: xR = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        xL_daily[day] = xL\n",
        "        xR_daily[day] = xR\n",
        "        adv_daily[day] = xL - xR\n",
        "        uv_daily[day] = uv_mult\n",
        "        a_daily[day] = a_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "    return xL_daily, xR_daily, adv_daily, uv_daily, a_daily\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_year(xL1, xR1, adv1, uv1, title=\"\"):\n",
        "    days = len(xL1)\n",
        "    t = np.arange(days)\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, xL1, label=\"xL (left-handed)\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, xR1, label=\"xR (right-handed)\", linestyle=\"--\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (end-of-day)\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "    plt.title(title + \" — advantage and UV severity proxy\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, adv1, label=\"adv = xL - xR\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, uv1, label=\"UV severity multiplier\", linestyle=\":\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Value\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Run 1-year comparison: with seasonality vs without ---\n",
        "common = dict(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,\n",
        "    b=2.0,\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# No seasonality\n",
        "xL0, xR0, adv0, uv0, a0 = simulate_year(**common, seasonal_uv_amp=0.0, seasonal_a_amp=0.0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# With UV seasonality (damage stronger/weaker over the year)\n",
        "xLs, xRs, advs, uvs, as_ = simulate_year(**common, seasonal_uv_amp=0.6, seasonal_a_amp=0.0)\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_year(xL0, xR0, adv0, uv0, title=\"1-year toy — NO seasonality (UV constant)\")\n",
        "plot_year(xLs, xRs, advs, uvs, title=\"1-year toy — WITH seasonality (UV varies)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final day (no season):  xL, xR, adv =\", xL0[-1], xR0[-1], adv0[-1])\n",
        "print(\"Final day (seasonal):   xL, xR, adv =\", xLs[-1], xRs[-1], advs[-1])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

        "\n",
        "eps = 1e-12  # prevents log(0)\n",
        "\n",
        "days = np.arange(len(xLs))\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "plt.plot(days, np.maximum(xLs, eps), label=\"xL\")\n",

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# Required arrays:\n",
        "# xL_daily, xR_daily\n",
        "# Optional arrays:\n",
        "# adv_daily, uv_daily, a_daily\n",
        "\n",
        "days = np.arange(len(xLs))\n",
        "\n",
        "data = {\n",
        "    \"day\": days,\n",
        "    \"xL\": np.array(xLs, dtype=float),\n",
        "    \"xR\": np.array(xRs, dtype=float),\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "if \"advs\" in globals():\n",
        "    data[\"adv\"] = np.array(advs, dtype=float)\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    data[\"adv\"] = data[\"xL\"] - data[\"xR\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "if \"uvs\" in globals():\n",
        "    data[\"uv_mult\"] = np.array(uvs, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "if \"as_\" in globals():\n",
        "    data[\"a_mult\"] = np.array(as_, dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
        "df.to_csv(\"year_run_timeseries.csv\", index=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Saved:\", \"year_run_timeseries.csv\")\n",
        "print(df.head())\n",
        "print(df.tail())"

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "eps = 1e-12\n",
        "days = np.arange(len(xLs))\n",
        "\n",
        "xL = np.array(xLs, dtype=float)\n",
        "xR = np.array(xRs, dtype=float)\n",
        "adv = np.array(advs, dtype=float) if \"advs\" in globals() else (xL - xR)\n",
        "uv = np.array(uvs, dtype=float) if \"uvs\" in globals() else None\n",
        "am = np.array(as_, dtype=float) if \"as_\" in globals() else None\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fig A: log scale growth\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "plt.title(\"Growth curves (log scale)\")\n",
        "plt.plot(days, np.maximum(xL, eps), label=\"xL\")\n",
        "plt.plot(days, np.maximum(xR, eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"xR\")\n",
        "plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "plt.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig(\"figA_growth_log.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fig B: linear scale growth\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "plt.title(\"Growth curves (linear scale)\")\n",
        "plt.plot(days, xL, label=\"xL\")\n",
        "plt.plot(days, xR, linestyle=\"--\", label=\"xR\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"x\")\n",
        "plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig(\"figB_growth_linear.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fig C: advantage with optional UV overlay (scaled)\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "plt.title(\"Advantage over time (xL - xR)\")\n",
        "plt.plot(days, adv, label=\"adv\")\n",
        "if uv is not None:\n",
        "    uv_scaled = uv / np.max(np.abs(uv)) * (np.max(np.abs(adv)) if np.max(np.abs(adv)) > 0 else 1.0)\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, uv_scaled, linestyle=\":\", label=\"UV (scaled)\")\n",
        "plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.5)\n",

        "plt.ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig(\"figC_advantage.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fig D: log magnitude of advantage (helps if adv spans orders)\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "plt.title(\"Advantage magnitude (log10)\")\n",
        "plt.plot(days, np.log10(np.maximum(np.abs(adv), eps)), label=\"log10(|adv|)\")\n",

        "plt.show()\n",

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "S1DrHWvftBZA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "def seasonal_factor(day, period_days=365, amp=0.6, phase=0.0):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Returns a multiplier in [1-amp, 1+amp] following a sinusoid over the year.\n",
        "    amp=0 -> no seasonality.\n",
        "    phase shifts the season (0 means peak at day ~period/4).\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    return 1.0 + amp * np.sin(2.0 * np.pi * (day / period_days) + phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "def simulate_year(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",          # \"AB\" means A then B each day; \"BA\" means B then A\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,                  # base growth rate in A window\n",
        "    b=2.0,                  # base damage rate in B window (UV analogue)\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",    # \"growth\", \"damage\", or \"both\"\n",
        "    seasonal_uv_amp=0.6,    # seasonality strength for UV/damage (0 -> none)\n",
        "    seasonal_a_amp=0.0,     # optional seasonality for growth/resources\n",
        "    uv_phase=0.0,\n",
        "    a_phase=0.0,\n",
        "):\n",
        "    dt = 1.0 / steps_per_day\n",
        "    half = steps_per_day // 2\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Chiral modifiers\n",
        "    aL0 = a * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    aR0 = a * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    bL0 = b * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "    bR0 = b * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "\n",
        "    xL = float(x0)\n",
        "    xR = float(x0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Store daily outputs (end-of-day)\n",
        "    xL_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    xR_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    adv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    uv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    a_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for day in range(days):\n",
        "        uv_mult = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_uv_amp, phase=uv_phase)\n",
        "        a_mult  = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_a_amp,  phase=a_phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Daily effective rates\n",
        "        aL = aL0 * a_mult\n",
        "        aR = aR0 * a_mult\n",
        "        bL = bL0 * uv_mult\n",
        "        bR = bR0 * uv_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Run one day with two windows (A and B) in the specified order\n",
        "        for step in range(steps_per_day):\n",
        "            gate = protocol[0] if step < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "            if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "                if xL >= xmin:\n",
        "                    xL += (aL * xL) * dt\n",
        "                if xR >= xmin:\n",
        "                    xR += (aR * xR) * dt\n",
        "            else:  # gate == \"B\" (UV/damage window)\n",
        "                xL -= (bL * xL) * dt\n",
        "                xR -= (bR * xR) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Floors\n",
        "            if xL < 0.0: xL = 0.0\n",
        "            if xR < 0.0: xR = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        xL_daily[day] = xL\n",
        "        xR_daily[day] = xR\n",
        "        adv_daily[day] = xL - xR\n",
        "        uv_daily[day] = uv_mult\n",
        "        a_daily[day] = a_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "    return xL_daily, xR_daily, adv_daily, uv_daily, a_daily\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_year(xL1, xR1, adv1, uv1, title=\"\"):\n",
        "    days = len(xL1)\n",
        "    t = np.arange(days)\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, xL1, label=\"xL (left-handed)\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, xR1, label=\"xR (right-handed)\", linestyle=\"--\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (end-of-day)\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "    plt.title(title + \" — advantage and UV severity proxy\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, adv1, label=\"adv = xL - xR\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, uv1, label=\"UV severity multiplier\", linestyle=\":\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Value\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Run 1-year comparison: with seasonality vs without ---\n",
        "common = dict(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,\n",
        "    b=2.0,\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# No seasonality\n",
        "xL0, xR0, adv0, uv0, a0 = simulate_year(**common, seasonal_uv_amp=0.0, seasonal_a_amp=0.0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# With UV seasonality (damage stronger/weaker over the year)\n",
        "xLs, xRs, advs, uvs, as_ = simulate_year(**common, seasonal_uv_amp=0.6, seasonal_a_amp=0.0)\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_year(xL0, xR0, adv0, uv0, title=\"1-year toy — NO seasonality (UV constant)\")\n",
        "plot_year(xLs, xRs, advs, uvs, title=\"1-year toy — WITH seasonality (UV varies)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final day (no season):  xL, xR, adv =\", xL0[-1], xR0[-1], adv0[-1])\n",
        "print(\"Final day (seasonal):   xL, xR, adv =\", xLs[-1], xRs[-1], advs[-1])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "akDDMTHStAQH"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "def seasonal_factor(day, period_days=365, amp=0.6, phase=0.0):\n",
        "    return 1.0 + amp * np.sin(2.0 * np.pi * (day / period_days) + phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "def simulate_year(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,\n",
        "    b=2.0,\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",\n",
        "    seasonal_uv_amp=0.6,\n",
        "    seasonal_a_amp=0.0,\n",
        "    uv_phase=0.0,\n",
        "    a_phase=0.0,\n",
        "    K=10.0,                 # NEW: carrying capacity / resource limit\n",
        "):\n",
        "    dt = 1.0 / steps_per_day\n",
        "    half = steps_per_day // 2\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Chiral modifiers\n",
        "    aL0 = a * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    aR0 = a * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    bL0 = b * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "    bR0 = b * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "\n",
        "    xL = float(x0)\n",
        "    xR = float(x0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    xL_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    xR_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    adv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    uv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    a_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for day in range(days):\n",
        "        uv_mult = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_uv_amp, phase=uv_phase)\n",
        "        a_mult  = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_a_amp,  phase=a_phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "        aL = aL0 * a_mult\n",
        "        aR = aR0 * a_mult\n",
        "        bL = bL0 * uv_mult\n",
        "        bR = bR0 * uv_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "        for step in range(steps_per_day):\n",
        "            gate = protocol[0] if step < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "            if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "                # NEW: resource-limited growth (logistic cap)\n",
        "                if xL >= xmin and K > 0:\n",
        "                    xL += (aL * xL * (1.0 - xL / K)) * dt\n",
        "                if xR >= xmin and K > 0:\n",
        "                    xR += (aR * xR * (1.0 - xR / K)) * dt\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                xL -= (bL * xL) * dt\n",
        "                xR -= (bR * xR) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "            if xL < 0.0: xL = 0.0\n",
        "            if xR < 0.0: xR = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        xL_daily[day] = xL\n",
        "        xR_daily[day] = xR\n",
        "        adv_daily[day] = xL - xR\n",
        "        uv_daily[day] = uv_mult\n",
        "        a_daily[day] = a_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "    return xL_daily, xR_daily, adv_daily, uv_daily, a_daily\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_year(xL1, xR1, adv1, uv1, title=\"\"):\n",
        "    days = len(xL1)\n",
        "    t = np.arange(days)\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, xL1, label=\"xL (left-handed)\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, xR1, label=\"xR (right-handed)\", linestyle=\"--\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (end-of-day)\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "    plt.title(title + \" — advantage and UV severity proxy\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, adv1, label=\"adv = xL - xR\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(t, uv1, label=\"UV severity multiplier\", linestyle=\":\")\n",
        "    plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Value\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Run 1-year comparison: with seasonality vs without ---\n",
        "common = dict(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,\n",
        "    b=2.0,\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",\n",
        "    K=10.0,   # NEW: set resource limit here\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "xL0, xR0, adv0, uv0, a0 = simulate_year(**common, seasonal_uv_amp=0.0, seasonal_a_amp=0.0)\n",
        "xLs, xRs, advs, uvs, as_ = simulate_year(**common, seasonal_uv_amp=0.6, seasonal_a_amp=0.0)\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_year(xL0, xR0, adv0, uv0, title=\"1-year toy — NO seasonality (UV constant) — with resource limit\")\n",
        "plot_year(xLs, xRs, advs, uvs, title=\"1-year toy — WITH seasonality (UV varies) — with resource limit\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final day (no season):  xL, xR, adv =\", xL0[-1], xR0[-1], adv0[-1])\n",
        "print(\"Final day (seasonal):   xL, xR, adv =\", xLs[-1], xRs[-1], advs[-1])"

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "def seasonal_factor(day, period_days=365, amp=0.6, phase=0.0):\n",
        "    return 1.0 + amp * np.sin(2.0 * np.pi * (day / period_days) + phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "def simulate_year(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    protocol=\"AB\",\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,\n",
        "    b=2.0,\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",\n",
        "    seasonal_uv_amp=0.6,\n",
        "    seasonal_a_amp=0.0,\n",
        "    uv_phase=0.0,\n",
        "    a_phase=0.0,\n",
        "    K=10.0,   # resource cap (carrying capacity)\n",
        "):\n",
        "    dt = 1.0 / steps_per_day\n",
        "    half = steps_per_day // 2\n",
        "\n",
        "    aL0 = a * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    aR0 = a * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"growth\", \"both\") else a\n",
        "    bL0 = b * (1.0 - chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "    bR0 = b * (1.0 + chiral_bias) if chirality_in in (\"damage\", \"both\") else b\n",
        "\n",
        "    xL = float(x0)\n",
        "    xR = float(x0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    xL_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    xR_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    adv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    uv_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "    a_daily = np.zeros(days)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for day in range(days):\n",
        "        uv_mult = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_uv_amp, phase=uv_phase)\n",
        "        a_mult  = seasonal_factor(day, period_days=days, amp=seasonal_a_amp, phase=a_phase)\n",
        "\n",
        "        aL = aL0 * a_mult\n",
        "        aR = aR0 * a_mult\n",
        "        bL = bL0 * uv_mult\n",
        "        bR = bR0 * uv_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "        for step in range(steps_per_day):\n",
        "            gate = protocol[0] if step < half else protocol[1]\n",
        "\n",
        "            if gate == \"A\":\n",
        "                # resource-limited growth (logistic)\n",
        "                if xL >= xmin and K > 0:\n",
        "                    xL += (aL * xL * (1.0 - xL / K)) * dt\n",
        "                if xR >= xmin and K > 0:\n",
        "                    xR += (aR * xR * (1.0 - xR / K)) * dt\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                xL -= (bL * xL) * dt\n",
        "                xR -= (bR * xR) * dt\n",
        "\n",
        "            if xL < 0.0: xL = 0.0\n",
        "            if xR < 0.0: xR = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        xL_daily[day] = xL\n",
        "        xR_daily[day] = xR\n",
        "        adv_daily[day] = xL - xR\n",
        "        uv_daily[day] = uv_mult\n",
        "        a_daily[day] = a_mult\n",
        "\n",
        "    return xL_daily, xR_daily, adv_daily, uv_daily, a_daily\n",
        "\n",
        "def save_run(tag, xL, xR, adv, uv, a_mult):\n",
        "    days = np.arange(len(xL))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # save npz\n",
        "    np.savez(\n",
        "        f\"{tag}_year_run_data.npz\",\n",
        "        xL_daily=xL, xR_daily=xR, adv_daily=adv, uv_daily=uv, a_daily=a_mult\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    # save csv\n",
        "    df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "        \"day\": days,\n",
        "        \"xL\": xL,\n",
        "        \"xR\": xR,\n",
        "        \"adv\": adv,\n",
        "        \"uv_mult\": uv,\n",
        "        \"a_mult\": a_mult\n",
        "    })\n",
        "    df.to_csv(f\"{tag}_year_run_timeseries.csv\", index=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # figures\n",
        "    eps = 1e-12\n",
        "\n",
        "    # log growth\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"{tag}: Growth curves (log scale)\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, np.maximum(xL, eps), label=\"xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, np.maximum(xR, eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"xR\")\n",
        "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.savefig(f\"{tag}_figA_growth_log.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # linear growth\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"{tag}: Growth curves (linear scale)\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, xL, label=\"xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, xR, linestyle=\"--\", label=\"xR\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.savefig(f\"{tag}_figB_growth_linear.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # advantage + UV\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"{tag}: Advantage and UV\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, adv, label=\"adv = xL - xR\")\n",
        "    uv_scaled = uv / np.max(np.abs(uv)) * (np.max(np.abs(adv)) if np.max(np.abs(adv)) > 0 else 1.0)\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, uv_scaled, linestyle=\":\", label=\"UV (scaled)\")\n",
        "    plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Value\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.savefig(f\"{tag}_figC_adv_uv.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"Saved: {tag}_year_run_data.npz, {tag}_year_run_timeseries.csv, and figA/figB/figC PNGs\")\n",
        "\n",
        "def compare_ab_ba(tag_ab, tag_ba):\n",
        "    ab = np.load(f\"{tag_ab}_year_run_data.npz\")\n",
        "    ba = np.load(f\"{tag_ba}_year_run_data.npz\")\n",
        "    days = np.arange(len(ab[\"xL_daily\"]))\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.title(\"AB vs BA (log scale) — xL and xR\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, np.maximum(ab[\"xL_daily\"], 1e-12), label=f\"{tag_ab} xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, np.maximum(ab[\"xR_daily\"], 1e-12), linestyle=\"--\", label=f\"{tag_ab} xR\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, np.maximum(ba[\"xL_daily\"], 1e-12), label=f\"{tag_ba} xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, np.maximum(ba[\"xR_daily\"], 1e-12), linestyle=\"--\", label=f\"{tag_ba} xR\")\n",
        "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.savefig(\"figD_AB_vs_BA_growth_log.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "    plt.title(\"AB vs BA — advantage\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, ab[\"adv_daily\"], label=f\"{tag_ab} adv\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(days, ba[\"adv_daily\"], label=f\"{tag_ba} adv\")\n",
        "    plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.savefig(\"figE_AB_vs_BA_adv.png\", dpi=200)\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(\"Saved: figD_AB_vs_BA_growth_log.png and figE_AB_vs_BA_adv.png\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# ------------------------\n",
        "# RUN: choose parameters\n",
        "# ------------------------\n",
        "params = dict(\n",
        "    days=365,\n",
        "    steps_per_day=200,\n",
        "    x0=0.20,\n",
        "    xmin=0.15,\n",
        "    a=3.0,\n",
        "    b=2.0,\n",
        "    chiral_bias=0.01,\n",
        "    chirality_in=\"both\",\n",
        "    seasonal_uv_amp=0.6,\n",
        "    seasonal_a_amp=0.0,\n",
        "    K=10.0,\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# AB run\n",
        "xL_ab, xR_ab, adv_ab, uv_ab, a_ab = simulate_year(**params, protocol=\"AB\")\n",
        "save_run(\"AB_cap\", xL_ab, xR_ab, adv_ab, uv_ab, a_ab)\n",
        "\n",
        "# BA run\n",
        "xL_ba, xR_ba, adv_ba, uv_ba, a_ba = simulate_year(**params, protocol=\"BA\")\n",
        "save_run(\"BA_cap\", xL_ba, xR_ba, adv_ba, uv_ba, a_ba)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Comparison plots\n",
        "compare_ab_ba(\"AB_cap\", \"BA_cap\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Final day AB:\", xL_ab[-1], xR_ab[-1], adv_ab[-1])\n",
        "print(\"Final day BA:\", xL_ba[-1], xR_ba[-1], adv_ba[-1])"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# CONFIG\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "OUTDIR = \"figs_pub\"\n",
        "os.makedirs(OUTDIR, exist_ok=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "AB_CSV = \"AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "BA_CSV = \"BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# If you’re running in this ChatGPT sandbox, use the uploaded BA path:\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(BA_CSV) and os.path.exists(\"/mnt/data/BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"):\n",
        "    BA_CSV = \"/mnt/data/BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Try the uploaded AB if present\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(AB_CSV) and os.path.exists(\"/mnt/data/AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"):\n",
        "    AB_CSV = \"/mnt/data/AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "def require(path, name):\n",
        "    if not os.path.exists(path):\n",
        "        raise FileNotFoundError(\n",
        "            f\"Missing {name} CSV: {path}\\n\"\n",
        "            f\"Put it in the working directory or set {name}_CSV to its path.\"\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "require(BA_CSV, \"BA\")\n",
        "# AB is optional: if missing, we’ll plot BA-only plus whatever comparisons are possible\n",
        "HAS_AB = os.path.exists(AB_CSV)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# LOAD\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "ba = pd.read_csv(BA_CSV)\n",
        "ab = pd.read_csv(AB_CSV) if HAS_AB else None\n",
        "\n",
        "def sanity(df, label):\n",
        "    needed = {\"day\", \"xL\", \"xR\", \"adv\", \"uv_mult\", \"a_mult\"}\n",
        "    missing = needed - set(df.columns)\n",
        "    if missing:\n",
        "        raise ValueError(f\"{label} missing columns: {missing}\")\n",
        "sanity(ba, \"BA\")\n",
        "if HAS_AB:\n",
        "    sanity(ab, \"AB\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# HELPERS\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def savefig(base_name):\n",
        "    png = os.path.join(OUTDIR, f\"{base_name}.png\")\n",
        "    pdf = os.path.join(OUTDIR, f\"{base_name}.pdf\")\n",
        "    plt.savefig(png, dpi=300, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
        "    plt.savefig(pdf, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
        "    print(\"Saved:\", png, \"and\", pdf)\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_multipliers(df, title, base_name):\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.2, 3.2))\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], df[\"uv_mult\"], label=\"UV multiplier\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], df[\"a_mult\"], linestyle=\"--\", label=\"A multiplier\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"Multiplier\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(base_name)\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_growth_log(df, title, base_name, eps=1e-12):\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.2, 3.6))\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], np.maximum(df[\"xL\"].values, eps), label=\"xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], np.maximum(df[\"xR\"].values, eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"xR\")\n",
        "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (log scale)\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(base_name)\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_growth_linear(df, title, base_name):\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.2, 3.6))\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], df[\"xL\"], label=\"xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], df[\"xR\"], linestyle=\"--\", label=\"xR\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(base_name)\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_adv(df, title, base_name):\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.2, 3.2))\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], df[\"adv\"], label=\"adv = xL − xR\")\n",
        "    plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(base_name)\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_adv_logmag(df, title, base_name, eps=1e-12):\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.2, 3.2))\n",
        "    plt.plot(df[\"day\"], np.log10(np.maximum(np.abs(df[\"adv\"].values), eps)), label=\"log10(|adv|)\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"log10(|adv|)\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(base_name)\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_scatter_adv_vs_uv(df, title, base_name):\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(4.2, 3.6))\n",
        "    plt.scatter(df[\"uv_mult\"], df[\"adv\"], s=12, alpha=0.7)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"UV multiplier\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    savefig(base_name)\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_zoom(df, title_prefix, base_name_prefix, day_max=60, eps=1e-12):\n",
        "    d = df[df[\"day\"] <= day_max].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.2, 3.6))\n",
        "    plt.plot(d[\"day\"], np.maximum(d[\"xL\"].values, eps), label=\"xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(d[\"day\"], np.maximum(d[\"xR\"].values, eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"xR\")\n",
        "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"{title_prefix} (Days 0–{day_max})\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(f\"{base_name_prefix}_growth_log_zoom0_{day_max}\")\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.2, 3.2))\n",
        "    plt.plot(d[\"day\"], d[\"adv\"], label=\"adv\")\n",
        "    plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"{title_prefix} advantage (Days 0–{day_max})\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(f\"{base_name_prefix}_adv_zoom0_{day_max}\")\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "def compute_metrics(df, label):\n",
        "    adv = df[\"adv\"].values\n",
        "    xL = df[\"xL\"].values\n",
        "    xR = df[\"xR\"].values\n",
        "    day = df[\"day\"].values\n",
        "    # AOI-like: cumulative positive advantage (discrete)\n",
        "    aoi_like = float(np.sum(np.maximum(adv, 0.0)))\n",
        "    # Peak advantage\n",
        "    peak_adv = float(np.max(adv))\n",
        "    # Final values\n",
        "    final = {\n",
        "        \"label\": label,\n",
        "        \"final_xL\": float(xL[-1]),\n",
        "        \"final_xR\": float(xR[-1]),\n",
        "        \"final_adv\": float(adv[-1]),\n",
        "        \"peak_adv\": peak_adv,\n",
        "        \"aoi_like_sum_pos_adv\": aoi_like,\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    return final\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# FIGURES (BA)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "plot_multipliers(ba, \"BA: Seasonal multipliers\", \"BA_multipliers\")\n",
        "plot_growth_log(ba, \"BA: Growth curves (log scale)\", \"BA_growth_log\")\n",
        "plot_growth_linear(ba, \"BA: Growth curves (linear scale)\", \"BA_growth_linear\")\n",
        "plot_adv(ba, \"BA: Advantage over time\", \"BA_adv\")\n",
        "plot_adv_logmag(ba, \"BA: Advantage magnitude (log10)\", \"BA_adv_logmag\")\n",
        "plot_scatter_adv_vs_uv(ba, \"BA: adv vs UV\", \"BA_adv_vs_uv\")\n",
        "plot_zoom(ba, \"BA\", \"BA\", day_max=60)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# FIGURES (AB) + COMPARISONS (if available)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "if HAS_AB:\n",
        "    plot_multipliers(ab, \"AB: Seasonal multipliers\", \"AB_multipliers\")\n",
        "    plot_growth_log(ab, \"AB: Growth curves (log scale)\", \"AB_growth_log\")\n",
        "    plot_growth_linear(ab, \"AB: Growth curves (linear scale)\", \"AB_growth_linear\")\n",
        "    plot_adv(ab, \"AB: Advantage over time\", \"AB_adv\")\n",
        "    plot_adv_logmag(ab, \"AB: Advantage magnitude (log10)\", \"AB_adv_logmag\")\n",
        "    plot_scatter_adv_vs_uv(ab, \"AB: adv vs UV\", \"AB_adv_vs_uv\")\n",
        "    plot_zoom(ab, \"AB\", \"AB\", day_max=60)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # AB vs BA growth (log) overlay\n",
        "    eps = 1e-12\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.6, 4.0))\n",
        "    plt.plot(ab[\"day\"], np.maximum(ab[\"xL\"].values, eps), label=\"AB xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(ab[\"day\"], np.maximum(ab[\"xR\"].values, eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"AB xR\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(ba[\"day\"], np.maximum(ba[\"xL\"].values, eps), label=\"BA xL\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(ba[\"day\"], np.maximum(ba[\"xR\"].values, eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"BA xR\")\n",
        "    plt.yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "    plt.title(\"AB vs BA: Growth curves (log scale)\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
        "    savefig(\"AB_vs_BA_growth_log\")\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # AB vs BA advantage overlay\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.6, 3.4))\n",
        "    plt.plot(ab[\"day\"], ab[\"adv\"], label=\"AB adv\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(ba[\"day\"], ba[\"adv\"], label=\"BA adv\")\n",
        "    plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "    plt.title(\"AB vs BA: Advantage over time\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(\"AB_vs_BA_adv\")\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Zoomed AB vs BA advantage (first 60 days)\n",
        "    dmax = 60\n",
        "    abz = ab[ab[\"day\"] <= dmax]\n",
        "    baz = ba[ba[\"day\"] <= dmax]\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(7.6, 3.4))\n",
        "    plt.plot(abz[\"day\"], abz[\"adv\"], label=\"AB adv\")\n",
        "    plt.plot(baz[\"day\"], baz[\"adv\"], label=\"BA adv\")\n",
        "    plt.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"Day\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"AB vs BA: Advantage (Days 0–{dmax})\")\n",
        "    plt.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    savefig(f\"AB_vs_BA_adv_zoom0_{dmax}\")\n",
        "    plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# METRICS TABLE\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "metrics = [compute_metrics(ba, \"BA\")]\n",
        "if HAS_AB:\n",
        "    metrics.insert(0, compute_metrics(ab, \"AB\"))\n",
        "\n",
        "metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics)\n",
        "metrics_df.to_csv(os.path.join(OUTDIR, \"summary_metrics.csv\"), index=False)\n",
        "print(\"Saved:\", os.path.join(OUTDIR, \"summary_metrics.csv\"))\n",
        "print(metrics_df)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nDone. Output folder:\", OUTDIR)"
      ],

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import math\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import matplotlib.image as mpimg\n",
        "\n",
        "FIGDIR = \"figs_pub\"\n",
        "OUTPNG = os.path.join(FIGDIR, \"PANEL_all.png\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Choose the exact PNGs you want in the panel, in order.\n",
        "# If a file is missing, it will be skipped (with a warning).\n",
        "panel_files = [\n",
        "    \"AB_vs_BA_growth_log.png\",\n",
        "    \"AB_vs_BA_adv.png\",\n",
        "    \"AB_figA_growth_log.png\",\n",
        "    \"AB_figC_adv_uv.png\",\n",
        "    \"BA_figA_growth_log.png\",\n",
        "    \"BA_figC_adv_uv.png\",\n",
        "    \"AB_multipliers.png\",\n",
        "    \"BA_multipliers.png\",\n",
        "    \"AB_adv_logmag.png\",\n",
        "    \"BA_adv_logmag.png\",\n",
        "    \"AB_adv_vs_uv.png\",\n",
        "    \"BA_adv_vs_uv.png\",\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "def existing_files(figdir, names):\n",
        "    found = []\n",
        "    for n in names:\n",
        "        p = os.path.join(figdir, n)\n",
        "        if os.path.exists(p):\n",
        "            found.append(p)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            print(\"Skipping missing:\", p)\n",
        "    return found\n",
        "\n",
        "paths = existing_files(FIGDIR, panel_files)\n",
        "if not paths:\n",
        "    raise FileNotFoundError(f\"No panel images found in {FIGDIR}. Check the filenames and folder.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Grid shape (auto)\n",
        "n = len(paths)\n",
        "cols = 3 if n >= 6 else 2\n",
        "rows = math.ceil(n / cols)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Panel sizing\n",
        "fig_w = 6.0 * cols\n",
        "fig_h = 3.6 * rows\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(rows, cols, figsize=(fig_w, fig_h))\n",
        "axes = axes.flatten() if hasattr(axes, \"flatten\") else [axes]\n",
        "\n",
        "for ax in axes:\n",
        "    ax.axis(\"off\")\n",
        "\n",
        "for i, path in enumerate(paths):\n",
        "    img = mpimg.imread(path)\n",
        "    axes[i].imshow(img)\n",
        "    # optional: add filename as a tiny title (comment out if you don’t want it)\n",
        "    axes[i].set_title(os.path.basename(path), fontsize=8)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig(OUTPNG, dpi=300, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
        "plt.close(fig)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Saved panel PNG:\", OUTPNG)"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import math\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import matplotlib.image as mpimg\n",
        "\n",
        "FIGDIR = \"figs_pub\"\n",
        "OUTPNG = os.path.join(FIGDIR, \"PANEL_compiled.png\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "# Helper: classify figures by keywords\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "def classify(fname):\n",
        "    f = fname.lower()\n",
        "    tags = []\n",
        "    if \"ab\" in f: tags.append(\"AB\")\n",
        "    if \"ba\" in f: tags.append(\"BA\")\n",
        "    if \"growth\" in f: tags.append(\"growth\")\n",
        "    if \"adv\" in f: tags.append(\"adv\")\n",
        "    if \"uv\" in f: tags.append(\"uv\")\n",
        "    if \"log\" in f: tags.append(\"log\")\n",
        "    if \"mult\" in f or \"season\" in f: tags.append(\"season\")\n",
        "    return tags\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "# Collect PNGs\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "pngs = [f for f in os.listdir(FIGDIR) if f.lower().endswith(\".png\")]\n",
        "if not pngs:\n",
        "    raise FileNotFoundError(f\"No PNGs found in {FIGDIR}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "info = []\n",
        "for f in pngs:\n",
        "    info.append({\n",
        "        \"file\": f,\n",
        "        \"path\": os.path.join(FIGDIR, f),\n",
        "        \"tags\": classify(f)\n",
        "    })\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "# Priority ordering (publication narrative)\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "priority = [\n",
        "    # Comparisons first\n",
        "    ([\"ab\", \"ba\", \"growth\", \"log\"], 0),\n",
        "    ([\"ab\", \"ba\", \"adv\"], 1),\n",
        "\n",
        "    # AB detailed behaviour\n",
        "    ([\"ab\", \"growth\", \"log\"], 2),\n",
        "    ([\"ab\", \"adv\", \"uv\"], 3),\n",
        "    ([\"ab\", \"adv\"], 4),\n",
        "\n",
        "    # BA control behaviour\n",
        "    ([\"ba\", \"growth\", \"log\"], 5),\n",
        "    ([\"ba\", \"adv\", \"uv\"], 6),\n",
        "    ([\"ba\", \"adv\"], 7),\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Environment / seasonality\n",
        "    ([\"season\"], 8),\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "def score(item):\n",
        "    f = item[\"file\"].lower()\n",
        "    best = 99\n",
        "    for keys, rank in priority:\n",
        "        if all(k in f for k in keys):\n",
        "            best = min(best, rank)\n",
        "    return best\n",
        "\n",
        "info.sort(key=score)\n",
        "\n",
        "paths = [i[\"path\"] for i in info]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Panel order:\")\n",
        "for i, p in enumerate(paths):\n",
        "    print(f\"{i+1:02d}  {os.path.basename(p)}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "# Build panel\n",
        "# ---------------------------------\n",
        "n = len(paths)\n",
        "cols = 3 if n >= 6 else 2\n",
        "rows = math.ceil(n / cols)\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_w = 6.0 * cols\n",
        "fig_h = 3.6 * rows\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(rows, cols, figsize=(fig_w, fig_h))\n",
        "axes = axes.flatten() if hasattr(axes, \"flatten\") else [axes]\n",
        "\n",
        "for ax in axes:\n",
        "    ax.axis(\"off\")\n",
        "\n",
        "for i, path in enumerate(paths):\n",
        "    img = mpimg.imread(path)\n",
        "    axes[i].imshow(img)\n",
        "    axes[i].set_title(os.path.basename(path), fontsize=8)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig(OUTPNG, dpi=300, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
        "plt.close(fig)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nSaved compiled panel:\", OUTPNG)"
      ],
      "metadata": {

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "AB_CSV = \"AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "BA_CSV = \"BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# If needed for your environment:\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(AB_CSV) and os.path.exists(\"/mnt/data/AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"):\n",
        "    AB_CSV = \"/mnt/data/AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(BA_CSV) and os.path.exists(\"/mnt/data/BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"):\n",
        "    BA_CSV = \"/mnt/data/BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "ab = pd.read_csv(AB_CSV)\n",
        "ba = pd.read_csv(BA_CSV)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Basic checks\n",
        "for df, name in [(ab, \"AB\"), (ba, \"BA\")]:\n",
        "    for col in [\"day\", \"xL\", \"xR\", \"adv\", \"uv_mult\", \"a_mult\"]:\n",
        "        if col not in df.columns:\n",
        "            raise ValueError(f\"{name} missing column: {col}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ensure alignment by day\n",
        "ab = ab.sort_values(\"day\").reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "ba = ba.sort_values(\"day\").reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Settings\n",
        "eps = 1e-12\n",
        "zoom_max_day = 70\n",
        "\n",
        "# Shared limits for fairness\n",
        "max_x = max(ab[\"xL\"].max(), ab[\"xR\"].max(), ba[\"xL\"].max(), ba[\"xR\"].max())\n",
        "min_x = max(eps, min(ab[\"xL\"][ab[\"xL\"]>0].min() if (ab[\"xL\"]>0).any() else eps,\n",
        "                   ab[\"xR\"][ab[\"xR\"]>0].min() if (ab[\"xR\"]>0).any() else eps,\n",
        "                   ba[\"xL\"][ba[\"xL\"]>0].min() if (ba[\"xL\"]>0).any() else eps,\n",
        "                   ba[\"xR\"][ba[\"xR\"]>0].min() if (ba[\"xR\"]>0).any() else eps))\n",
        "\n",
        "adv_max = max(ab[\"adv\"].abs().max(), ba[\"adv\"].abs().max())\n",
        "adv_max = adv_max if adv_max > 0 else 1.0\n",
        "\n",
        "def panel_label(ax, s):\n",
        "    ax.text(0.01, 0.98, s, transform=ax.transAxes, va=\"top\", ha=\"left\", fontsize=12, fontweight=\"bold\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create figure\n",
        "fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(12.5, 7.2))\n",
        "axs = axs.ravel()\n",
        "\n",
        "# (a) Multipliers (UV shown, A constant here)\n",
        "ax = axs[0]\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], ab[\"uv_mult\"], label=\"UV multiplier\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], ab[\"a_mult\"], linestyle=\"--\", label=\"A multiplier\")\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"Multiplier\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Seasonal forcing\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"a\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (b) Growth (log) zoom\n",
        "ax = axs[1]\n",
        "abz = ab[ab[\"day\"] <= zoom_max_day]\n",
        "baz = ba[ba[\"day\"] <= zoom_max_day]\n",
        "ax.plot(abz[\"day\"], np.maximum(abz[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"AB xL\")\n",
        "ax.plot(abz[\"day\"], np.maximum(abz[\"xR\"], eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"AB xR\")\n",
        "ax.plot(baz[\"day\"], np.maximum(baz[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"BA xL\")\n",
        "ax.plot(baz[\"day\"], np.maximum(baz[\"xR\"], eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"BA xR\")\n",
        "ax.set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(min_x, max_x)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(f\"Growth (log), days 0–{zoom_max_day}\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"b\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (c) Advantage zoom\n",
        "ax = axs[2]\n",
        "ax.plot(abz[\"day\"], abz[\"adv\"], label=\"AB adv\")\n",
        "ax.plot(baz[\"day\"], baz[\"adv\"], label=\"BA adv\")\n",
        "ax.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(-0.05*adv_max, 1.05*adv_max)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"adv = xL − xR\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(f\"Advantage, days 0–{zoom_max_day}\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"c\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (d) Advantage full year\n",
        "ax = axs[3]\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], ab[\"adv\"], label=\"AB adv\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ba[\"day\"], ba[\"adv\"], label=\"BA adv\")\n",
        "ax.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(-0.05*adv_max, 1.05*adv_max)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Advantage, full year\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"d\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (e) adv vs UV scatter (AB + BA)\n",
        "ax = axs[4]\n",
        "ax.scatter(ab[\"uv_mult\"], ab[\"adv\"], s=14, alpha=0.7, label=\"AB\")\n",
        "ax.scatter(ba[\"uv_mult\"], ba[\"adv\"], s=14, alpha=0.7, label=\"BA\")\n",
        "ax.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"UV multiplier\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Advantage vs UV (phase portrait)\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"e\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (f) Growth (log) full year\n",
        "ax = axs[5]\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], np.maximum(ab[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"AB xL\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], np.maximum(ab[\"xR\"], eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"AB xR\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ba[\"day\"], np.maximum(ba[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"BA xL\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ba[\"day\"], np.maximum(ba[\"xR\"], eps), linestyle=\"--\", label=\"BA xR\")\n",
        "ax.set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(min_x, max_x)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Growth (log), full year\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"f\")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.suptitle(\"Ordering gates chirality expression: AB vs BA under seasonal UV (resource-limited)\", y=1.02, fontsize=13)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "\n",
        "out_png = \"FIG_main_AB_vs_BA.png\"\n",
        "plt.savefig(out_png, dpi=300, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "print(\"Saved:\", out_png)"
      ],
      "metadata": {

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# INPUT CSVs\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "AB_CSV = \"AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "BA_CSV = \"BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(AB_CSV) and os.path.exists(\"/mnt/data/AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"):\n",
        "    AB_CSV = \"/mnt/data/AB_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(BA_CSV) and os.path.exists(\"/mnt/data/BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"):\n",
        "    BA_CSV = \"/mnt/data/BA_cap_year_run_timeseries.csv\"\n",
        "\n",
        "ab = pd.read_csv(AB_CSV).sort_values(\"day\").reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "ba = pd.read_csv(BA_CSV).sort_values(\"day\").reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "for df, name in [(ab, \"AB\"), (ba, \"BA\")]:\n",
        "    for col in [\"day\", \"xL\", \"xR\", \"adv\", \"uv_mult\", \"a_mult\"]:\n",
        "        if col not in df.columns:\n",
        "            raise ValueError(f\"{name} missing column: {col}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# OUTPUT\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "OUTPNG = \"FIG_main_AB_vs_BA_tight.png\"\n",
        "OUTDIR = \"figs_pub\"\n",
        "os.makedirs(OUTDIR, exist_ok=True)\n",
        "OUTPNG = os.path.join(OUTDIR, OUTPNG)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# SETTINGS\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "eps = 1e-12\n",
        "zoom_max_day = 70\n",
        "\n",
        "# Shared limits for fair comparison\n",
        "max_x = max(ab[\"xL\"].max(), ba[\"xL\"].max())\n",
        "min_x = max(eps, min(\n",
        "    ab.loc[ab[\"xL\"] > 0, \"xL\"].min() if (ab[\"xL\"] > 0).any() else eps,\n",
        "    ba.loc[ba[\"xL\"] > 0, \"xL\"].min() if (ba[\"xL\"] > 0).any() else eps\n",
        "))\n",
        "\n",
        "adv_max = max(ab[\"adv\"].abs().max(), ba[\"adv\"].abs().max())\n",
        "adv_max = adv_max if adv_max > 0 else 1.0\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# HELPERS\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def panel_label(ax, s):\n",
        "    ax.text(0.01, 0.98, s, transform=ax.transAxes, va=\"top\", ha=\"left\",\n",
        "            fontsize=12, fontweight=\"bold\")\n",
        "\n",
        "def cum_pos_adv(series):\n",
        "    return np.cumsum(np.maximum(series, 0.0))\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# PREP DATA\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "abz = ab[ab[\"day\"] <= zoom_max_day]\n",
        "baz = ba[ba[\"day\"] <= zoom_max_day]\n",
        "\n",
        "ab_cum = cum_pos_adv(ab[\"adv\"].values)\n",
        "ba_cum = cum_pos_adv(ba[\"adv\"].values)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# FIGURE: 2x3, reduced clutter\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(12.5, 7.2))\n",
        "axs = axs.ravel()\n",
        "\n",
        "# (a) Seasonal forcing (UV shown, A constant here)\n",
        "ax = axs[0]\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], ab[\"uv_mult\"], label=\"UV multiplier\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], ab[\"a_mult\"], linestyle=\"--\", label=\"A multiplier\")\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"Multiplier\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Seasonal forcing\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"a\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (b) Growth (log), early — show xL only (AB vs BA)\n",
        "ax = axs[1]\n",
        "ax.plot(abz[\"day\"], np.maximum(abz[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"AB xL\")\n",
        "ax.plot(baz[\"day\"], np.maximum(baz[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"BA xL\")\n",
        "ax.set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(min_x, max_x)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(f\"Growth (log), early (0–{zoom_max_day})\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"b\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (c) Advantage, early\n",
        "ax = axs[2]\n",
        "ax.plot(abz[\"day\"], abz[\"adv\"], label=\"AB adv\")\n",
        "ax.plot(baz[\"day\"], baz[\"adv\"], label=\"BA adv\")\n",
        "ax.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(-0.05*adv_max, 1.05*adv_max)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"adv = xL − xR\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(f\"Advantage, early (0–{zoom_max_day})\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"c\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (d) Cumulative positive advantage (AOI-like memory)\n",
        "ax = axs[3]\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], ab_cum, label=\"AB cum[adv+]\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ba[\"day\"], ba_cum, label=\"BA cum[adv+]\")\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"cumulative adv+\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Cumulative advantage (AOI-like)\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"d\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (e) Advantage vs UV (phase portrait) — AB loop vs BA near-zero\n",
        "ax = axs[4]\n",
        "ax.scatter(ab[\"uv_mult\"], ab[\"adv\"], s=14, alpha=0.7, label=\"AB\")\n",
        "ax.scatter(ba[\"uv_mult\"], ba[\"adv\"], s=14, alpha=0.7, label=\"BA\")\n",
        "ax.axhline(0, linewidth=0.7)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"UV multiplier\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"adv\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Advantage vs UV\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"e\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# (f) Growth (log), full year — xL only (AB vs BA)\n",
        "ax = axs[5]\n",
        "ax.plot(ab[\"day\"], np.maximum(ab[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"AB xL\")\n",
        "ax.plot(ba[\"day\"], np.maximum(ba[\"xL\"], eps), label=\"BA xL\")\n",
        "ax.set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
        "ax.set_ylim(min_x, max_x)\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"Day\"); ax.set_ylabel(\"x (log)\")\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Growth (log), full year\")\n",
        "ax.grid(True, which=\"both\", linestyle=\":\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
        "panel_label(ax, \"f\")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.suptitle(\"Ordering gates chirality expression: AB vs BA under seasonal UV (resource-limited)\", y=1.02, fontsize=13)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig(OUTPNG, dpi=300, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Saved:\", OUTPNG)"

          "height": 609

        "outputId": "47920824-f61d-48f6-84e3-dea545badccd"

              "<Figure size 1250x720 with 6 Axes>"

          "metadata": {}

        {
          "output_type": "stream",
